#| "<link linkend=\"dlg-config-editor\">configuration dialog</link>."
msgid ""
"'Fill-in-the-blank' is a powerful way to practice in &kwordquiz;. It is a "
"special kind of question and answer quiz that needs to be described in more "
"detail."
msgstr ""
"Tühikute kasutamine on &kwordquiz;i üks tõhusamaid sõnavara omandamise "
"viise. See on spetsiaalne küsimuste-vastuste viktoriin, mida tuleb veidi "
"üksikasjalikumalt kirjeldada. Kasutamiseks tuleb see sisse lülitada <link "
"linkend=\"dlg-config-editor\">seadistusdtedialoogis</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336
#, no-c-format
msgid "Consider the following table. It could be a vocabulary in &kwordquiz;:"
msgstr ""
"Vaata järgmist tabelit. Selline võib näiteks välja näha &kwordquiz;i "
"sõnavaradokument:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "English"
msgstr "Inglise"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid "German"
msgstr "Saksa"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>1</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>1</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:352 index.docbook:358 index.docbook:364 index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "We own a computer"
msgstr "We own a computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir besitzen einen Computer"
msgstr "Wir besitzen einen Computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>2</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>2</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir [besitzen] einen Computer"
msgstr "Wir [besitzen] einen Computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>3</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>3</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir [besitzen einen] Computer"
msgstr "Wir [besitzen einen] Computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:369
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>4</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>4</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir [besitzen] einen [Computer]"
msgstr "Wir [besitzen] einen [Computer]"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The important thing to note is the placement of the brackets. They tell "
"&kwordquiz; how the quiz should be performed."
msgstr ""
"Oluline on tähele panna sulgude asukohta. Need teevad &kwordquiz;ile "
"selgeks, mil moel viktoriini korraldada."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In 1. there are no brackets. Assuming English is the question and German the "
"answer you have to give the entire expression 'Wir besitzen einen Computer' "
"for a correct answer."
msgstr ""
"Esimeses paaris sulge ei ole. Oletades, et ingliskeelne lause on küsimus ja "
"saksakeelne vastus, tuleb õige vastusena sisestada terve lause 'Wir besitzen "
"einen Computer'."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In 2. &kwordquiz; would display the question but also 'Wir ........ einen "
"Computer'. For a correct answer it is sufficient to write 'besitzen'."
msgstr ""
"Teises paaris näitab &kwordquiz; küsimust, aga ka vastust kujul "
"'Wir ........ einen Computer'. Õige vastuse jaoks piisab sõna 'besitzen' "
"kirjutamiseks."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"3. shows that a blank can consist of more than one word. The correct answer "
"is 'besitzen einen'."
msgstr ""
"Kolmandas paaris on tühikus enam kui üks sõna. Õige vastus on 'besitzen "
"einen'."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:389
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In 4. there are two separate blanks. To specify that in the answer you "
#| "have to write 'besitzen; Computer', i.e separate the blanks with a "
#| "semicolon in order to get a correct answer."
msgid ""
"In 4. there are two separate blanks. To specify that in the answer you have "
"to write 'besitzen; Computer', &ie; separate the blanks with a semicolon in "
"order to get a correct answer."
msgstr ""
"Neljandas paaris on kaks eraldi tühikut. Sellisel juhul tuleb vastuseks anda "
"'besitzen; Computer', s.t. eraldada erinevate tühikute vastused "
"semikooloniga, sest ainult siis loetakse vastus õigeks."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:392
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Marked blanks are only of relevance if they appear in the answer. Otherwise "
"the brackets are ignored. Furthermore, brackets have no effect in multiple "
"choice quizzes. To simplify the creation of 'Fill-in-the-blank' vocabularies "
"there are menu commands to mark and unmark blanks. Of course you can also "
"just type the brackets. &kwordquiz; checks the syntax. If the text appears "
"in red there is something wrong with the brackets and a quiz cannot be "
"started."
msgstr ""
"Tühikute märkimisel on mõtet ainult vastuste korral, sest muidu sulge "
"lihtsalt ignoreeritakse. Sulgudel ei ole mingit rolli ka mitme valikuga "
"viktoriinis. Tühikuid kasutavate sõnaraamatudokumentide loomise "
"lihtsustamiseks on nende lisamise ja eemaldamise käsud toodud ära menüüs. "
"&kwordquiz; kontrollib ka süntaksit. Kui tekst värvub punaseks, on sulgudega "
"midagi valesti ja viktoriini ei saa käivitada."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid "Printing"
msgstr "Trükkimine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:399
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kwordquiz; provides the ability to print vocabulary documents in several "
#| "different ways. When selecting <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Print...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> you are "
#| "presented with the standard &kde; print dialog. In order to get access to "
#| "the special &kwordquiz; features you need to click on the "
#| "<guibutton>Options&gt;&gt;</guibutton> to see the <guilabel>Vocabulary "
#| "Options</guilabel> tab. On this tab you can select to print the document "
#| "as a vocabulary list (&ie; as displayed in the editor), a vocabulary "
#| "exam, or as flashcards."
msgid ""
"&kwordquiz; provides the ability to print vocabulary documents in several "
"different ways. The printing options are available in the &kwordquiz; "
"editor. When selecting <guibutton>Print...</guibutton> you are presented "
"with a menu where you can select to print the document as a vocabulary list "
"(&ie; as displayed in the editor), a vocabulary exam, or as flashcards. Once "
"the mode is selected, you will be presented with the standard &kde; print "
"dialog."
msgstr ""
"&kwordquiz; võimaldab sõnavaradokumente väga mitmel moel trükkida. Kui valid "
"menüükäsu <menuchoice><guimenu>Fail</guimenu><guimenuitem>Trüki...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>, ilmub &kde; tavapärane trükkimisdialoog. "
"&kwordquiz;i spetsiaalsete võimaluste kasutamiseks klõpsa nupule "
"<guibutton>Valikud&gt;&gt;</guibutton>, mis toob nähtavale "
"<guilabel>sõnavaravalikute</guilabel> kaardi. Sellel saab valida dokumendi "
"trükkimise sõnavaraloendina (&ie; sellisena, nagu seda näitab redaktor), "
"sõnavaraeksamina või sähvikutena."

